      "text": "All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 19.812,
      "end": 31.418,
      "text": "The hairs once gathered together and lamented the unhappiness of their lot, exposed as they were to dangers on all sides, and lacking the strength and the courage to hold their own.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 32.198,
      "end": 39.061,
      "text": "Men, dogs, birds, and beasts of prey were all their enemies, and killed and devoured them daily.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 39.942,
      "end": 46.745,
      "text": "And sooner than endure such persecution any longer, they won an all determined to end their miserable lives.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 48.06,
      "end": 55.224,
      "text": "Thus result and desperate, they rushed in a body towards a neighbouring pool, intending to drown themselves.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 56.485,
      "end": 67.39,
      "text": "On the bank were sitting a number of frogs, who, when they heard the noise of the hairs as they ran, with one accord leaped into the water and hid themselves in the depths.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 68.111,
      "end": 74.034,
      "text": "Then, one of the older hairs, who was wiser than the rest, cried out to his companions.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 75.055,
      "end": 76.295,
      "text": "Stop, my friends!",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 76.856,
      "end": 77.536,
      "text": "Take heart!",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 78.337,
      "end": 80.999,
      "text": "Don't let us destroy ourselves after all.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 81.72,
      "end": 89.667,
      "text": "See, hear our creatures who are afraid of us, and who must therefore be still more timid than ourselves.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 90.828,
      "end": 93.751,
      "text": "End of the hairs and the frogs.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
